article.headline: Dartmouth 63, Penn 60
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Dan Biber converted a three-point play with eight seconds left to give Dartmouth a 63-60 victory over Pennsylvania on Saturday night. Alex Barnett had 24 points for Dartmouth and Biber a career-high 17 as the Big Green (4-14, 2-2 Ivy League) snapped a 23-game losing streak against the Quakers. Tyler Bernardini, who led the Quakers (5-11, 1-1) with 22 points, got off a clean look from 27 feet at the buzzer, but the shot bounded off the left side of the rim. Cameron Lewis added 12 points and Brennan Votel with 10 for Penn. Josh Riddle came up with steals on consecutive Penn possessions that led to a driving layup by Pride and David Rufful's jumper with 1:28 on the clock for a 60-59 Dartmouth lead. Bernardini hit 1-of-2 free throws to tie the game at 60 with 37 seconds to play, setting up Biber's heroics.
